    "client_msg_id": "11337065-4beb-4d48-9115-2ba8e42ba792",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "<@UKDM3GLAJ> ruining my image was definitely a concern from my time in Smalltalk.  Undo and some sensible process isolation go a long way.  Comfort comes from being able to answer: would clicking this break anything?  One fun dynamic way to tell is to speculatively execute the actions available from a given state recording their effects.  Then you can indicate which is which: does it change the view, the document, a broader model.",
    "user": "UA14TGLTC",
    "ts": "1592965979.424200",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "blocks": [
